"title": "5592: treaty",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5592",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>A formal agreement between individuals or nations, promising commitment to each other's interests. Israel was forbidden to enter into such agreements with other nations in the promised land.</p>\n<h2>Treaties between individuals</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:3-1Sam18:4\">1SA 18:3–18:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen21:22-Gen21:32\">GEN 21:22–21:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen26:26-Gen26:31\">GEN 26:26–26:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:8\">1SA 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam20:16-1Sam20:17\">1SA 20:16–20:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam22:8\">1SA 22:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam23:18\">1SA 23:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:12-2Sam3:13\">2SA 3:12–3:13</a></p>\n<h2>Treaties between individuals acting on behalf of their nation</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs5:12-1Kgs5:18\">1KI 5:12–5:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs15:18-1Kgs15:19\">1KI 15:18–15:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa33:8\">ISA 33:8</a> <em>Probably the agreement made when Hezekiah paid large sums to Sennacherib (<a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs18:14\">2Ki 18:14</a>)</em>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:12-Ezek17:14\">EZK 17:12–17:14</a></p>\n<h2>Treaties between cities or nations</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh9:3-Josh9:16\">JOS 9:3–9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh10:1\">JOS 10:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh11:18-Josh11:19\">JOS 11:18–11:19</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam11:1-1Sam11:2\">1SA 11:1–11:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos12:1\">HOS 12:1</a></p>\n<h2>Treaties entered into should be honoured</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek17:15-Ezek17:18\">EZK 17:15–17:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer34:8-Jer34:20\">JER 34:8–34:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:22-Dan11:24\">DAN 11:22–11:24</a> <em>“he will act deceitfully” (verse 23), is a reference to Antiochus Epiphanes (of the Seleucid dynasty) who reneged on the friendship shown to Egypt</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos10:4\">HOS 10:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:9-Amos1:10\">AMO 1:9–1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:15\">GAL 3:15</a></p>\n<h2>Israel forbidden to enter into treaties with other nations in the promised land</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut7:1-Deut7:2\">DEU 7:1–7:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod23:31-Exod23:32\">EXO 23:31–23:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:11-Exod34:12\">EXO 34:11–34:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:15-Exod34:16\">EXO 34:15–34:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut23:6\">DEU 23:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:34\">1KI 20:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs20:42-1Kgs20:43\">1KI 20:42–20:43</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezra9:12\">EZR 9:12</a></p>",
